4: There's a disturbance in our trajectory.
21:
I know what you're here for... But 
unfortunately, I'm too beautiful to die.
32:
Yes. I'm quite certain of the fact. 
And you are?
36:
Well, well... Isn't this a delectable 
surprise?
38:
I'm Belsidia. Otherwise known as the 
Wicked Witch of the Rift.
41: It's very nice to meet you, Belsidia.
45:
My! Aren't you just the sweetest 
cupcake? I could gobble you up!
53:
Oh... My bad, sugar plum. I got a little 
excited...
56:
I've never had such a cute guest, you 
know. I'd better see that your stay is 
pleasurable.
60:
...But there was nothing there…
Did you use a form of teleportation?
63:
This is the Rift, buttercup. My very own 
space, far away from the stars. All it 
takes is a little magic, and you can 
have all the sweets you want.
65:
Of course, it's nothing impressive when 
compared to the World Flipper.
68: You know of the World Flipper?
70: I do. There isn't one here though.
74:
Impossible. The World Flipper exists in 
all places.
77:
Hehe... Like I said, this is the Rift. The 
space in between. Not to mention, the 
only thing predictable about life is its 
unpredictability.
79:
...But I'm turning your head with all this 
talk.
Sit down. The tea's going to go cold.
86:
Happy you like it. I import my leaves 
from several different worlds.
89: You can travel to different worlds?
92:
Sure, if there's a crack I can hitch the 
Rift up to. Truth is, muffin, I could send 
you home with a snap of my fingers.
95:
But I can't return yet. I must locate my 
companions.
97:
They are important to me.
Belsidia, would you help me search for 
them?
101:
Of course, sweet pea. 
How could I say no to you?
115:
Stella! Thank goodness! We were 
looking all over for—
125:
Oh my... You're the champion Light, 
aren't you?
127:
Well, haven't you turned into the 
cutest honey bunny?
131: Belsidia! You should've fallen by my—
138:
Really, Light. I don't think that kind of 
talk's appropriate for young ears.
141:
Simmer down. I'm done with being 
bad. I even cut off ties with the fiends.
143:
Besides, it's not every day you meet 
a cinnamon roll like Stella. Can you 
blame me for wanting to lend a hand?
148:
Traitor! You must not be left to wander 
at will!
152:
The funny thing is, I don't remember 
asking for permission.
157:
Light, we are currently safe because of 
Belsidia. And she has offered to guide 
us home.
158:
She also reminds me of Alk—both host 
excellent tea parties.
162:
You coming, Light? Or do you want to 
be left all alone in this cold, scary 
place?
164:
O, darkness found in each vale and 
scar,
Void that enfolds each twinkling star,
Bear us hence to a world away far!
172:
The Wicked Witch Belsidia. She was 
once a great sorceress, but her lust for 
power poisoned her heart.
173:
She made her way to the Dark Throne, 
turning her back on the world of 
mortals. She is faithless... beyond 
redemption.
177:
*sigh* What a cutie... I'd be mad to 
trust her to a butterfingered 
champion.
